summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on the Democratic Republic of the Congo, particularly 1616 (2005) and 1649 (2005),
Determined to monitor compliance with the arms embargo and enforce measures against violators,
Noting the situation in the Democratic Republic of the Congo remains a threat to international peace and security,
Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter,

1. Requests the Secretary-General to re-establish the Group of Experts within 30 days, expiring on 31 July 2006;
2. Requests the Group to continue its mandate, update the Committee by 10 April 2006, and report to the Council by 10 July 2006;
3. Demands cooperation with the Group, ensuring their safety, and unhindered access to persons, documents, and sites;
4. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
